  <refnamediv>
    <refname>nrz</refname>
    <refpurpose>NRZ pulse shaping</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   y = nrz(b,osf)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>b:</term>
      <listitem><para> input binary sequence</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>osf:</term>
      <listitem><para> Over-Sampling Factor</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>y:</term>
      <listitem><para> output NRZ signal</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function convert a binary sequence (0 and 1) to a sequence of -1 and 1, where each
symbol is repeated (according to the osf parameter).
To say it another way, this is the same as using as a pulse-shaping filter a moving average of length equal to the symbol period.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

